DateReviewed: 2026-07-03
Description: Our article today talks about updating Kubernetes deployments without recreation. They explain that there are a lot of moving parts in an update, and to have an interruption free deployment requires lots of little things. Now, this is sort of a tutorial on how to do things - as they walk us through figuring out where the service port is; what the version of the image is, and how many replicas we have running; then show us how to modify/increase all of these items. Pretty compact but good walkthrough.
BottomLine: Solid walkthrough on doing modifications to a Kubernetes deployment
